Title: _app.seller.reports._index page
Route file: web/routes/_app.seller.reports._index.tsx
Suggested path: /app/seller/reports

Role/Purpose
- Provide seller-facing reports interface with sales overview, channel breakdown, assortment performance, compliance monitoring, and settlement tracking.
- Enable sellers to track sales metrics, monitor channel performance, assess compliance, and review settlement cycles.

Primary UI Components
- `PageHeader` with title "Reports" and description.
- Sales overview cards: Total GMV, Order count, Average order value, Delivered rate, Pending count, Cancelled count, GMV change.
- Trend chart/table showing daily sales over 14-day period.
- Channel breakdown table: Channel, Payment method, GMV, Orders, Share.
- Assortment performance table: Name, GMV, Orders, Share, Last order date.
- Compliance section: Summary (healthy, monitor, action counts), Listings table, Tasks table.
- Settlements section: Summary (cycles, orders, amount), Cycles table, Next payout card.
- Status badges: healthy, monitor, action, Complete, In progress, Attention needed.

Data Dependencies
- Loader calls `context.api.order.findMany()` with filter for last 30 days, selecting: `id`, `orderDate`, `status`, `channel`, `total`, `payment.paymentMethod`, `sellerProduct.assortment.id`, `sellerProduct.assortment.name` (first 250, sorted by orderDate descending).
- Loader aggregates order data to compute sales overview, trends, channel breakdown, assortment performance, compliance scores, and settlement cycles.
- Trend computed over `TREND_DAYS = 14` period.
- Compliance scores computed with minimum threshold `MIN_COMPLIANCE_SCORE = 35`.
- Weekly summaries use ISO week calculation (`getIsoWeek` helper).
- On API error, orders array defaults to empty array (graceful degradation).

